# ============================================================================
# TIPS & TRICKS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Hot-reload configuration:
#    staticwall reload
#
# 2. Run with auto-reload (watches config file for changes):
#    staticwall --watch
#
# 3. Test configuration before daemonizing:
#    staticwall -v -f
#
# 4. Use absolute paths if ~ doesn't work:
#    path /home/username/Pictures/wallpaper.png
#
# 5. Organize wallpapers in folders and use directory cycling:
#    mkdir -p ~/Pictures/Wallpapers/{Nature,Abstract,Space}
#    path ~/Pictures/Wallpapers/Nature/
#
# 6. Check logs for errors:
#    staticwall -f -v  (run in foreground with verbose logging)
#
# 7. Different configs for different scenarios:
#    staticwall -c ~/.config/staticwall/work.vibe
#    staticwall -c ~/.config/staticwall/home.vibe
#
# 8. Recommended cycling durations:
#    - Quick:    300 (5 minutes)
#    - Moderate: 900 (15 minutes)
#    - Slow:    1800 (30 minutes)
#    - Hourly:  3600 (1 hour)
#
# 9. Directory cycling:
#    Just set path to a directory with trailing slash:
#    path ~/Pictures/Wallpapers/
#    This automatically loads all PNG and JPEG files
#    Much easier than listing files manually!
#
# 10. Live shader wallpapers:
#     - Installed to ~/.config/staticwall/shaders/ on first run
#     - Just use the filename: shader plasma.glsl
#     - Renders at ~60 FPS with minimal CPU usage
#     - Control animation speed: shader_speed 2.0 (2x faster) or 0.5 (slower)
#     - Create your own shaders! See shaders/README.md
#
# 11. Control the daemon:
#     staticwall kill      # Stop daemon
#     staticwall reload    # Reload config
#     staticwall next      # Skip to next wallpaper
#     staticwall pause     # Pause cycling
#     staticwall resume    # Resume cycling
#     staticwall current   # Show current wallpaper
#
# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# Problem: "Configuration file not found"
# Solution: Make sure this file is at ~/.config/staticwall/config.vibe
#
# Problem: "Failed to parse VIBE config"
# Solution: Check for mismatched braces { } and brackets [ ]
#
# Problem: Wallpaper not showing
# Solution: Verify the image file exists: ls -la ~/Pictures/wallpaper.png
#
# Problem: Monitor not recognized
# Solution: Check exact monitor name with: swaymsg -t get_outputs
#
# Problem: Wallpapers not cycling
# Solution: Ensure duration > 0 and path points to a directory (with trailing /)
#
# Problem: Shader not found
# Solution: Shaders are in ~/.config/staticwall/shaders/ (copied on first run)
#          Use just the filename: shader plasma.glsl
#
# Problem: Black screen with shader
# Solution: Check logs with: staticwall -f -v
#          Ensure your GPU supports OpenGL ES 2.0
#
# Problem: Shader performance issues
# Solution: Shaders run at 60 FPS. If laggy, check GPU drivers
#
